The paper deals with the issue of pruning a given interleaver, which is a common technique used in information theory and coding theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of pruning on the structural properties of the permutation, which falls under the scope of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel lifting method, which involves the use of dummy symbols, and this can be categorized under cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper mentions the application of pruning to concatenated codes, which is related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
